  "text": "The second most abundant protein of the isolated Hermes body is the first enzyme in glycolysis, Hexokinase 1 (electronic supplementary material, table S2). This is the most abundant protein in the metabolism category (figure 4a). Hexokinase 1 localizes to the Hermes body of sperm in the epididymal lumen (figure 4b). Lactate dehydrogenase C the 25th most abundant protein of the category is concentrated largely in the Hermes body (figure 4c). All other glycolytic enzymes are characterized by proteomics albeit at markedly different abundances (figure 4d). Thus, the Hermes body concentrates GLUT-3 and all glycolytic enzymes, extending the observations of Yuan et al. [CITATION_1] , who observed only the soluble glycolytic enzymes by their two-dimensional gels.",
